☀️🌧️ Weather App
Welcome to the Weather App ⛅ project! This simple and intuitive app allows users to enter a city name 🌍 and get real-time temperature and weather conditions using the OpenWeatherMap API. Built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, this app provides up-to-date weather details in a clean and user-friendly interface. 🌐

🔧 Tech Stack

HTML 📝: Provides the structure of the weather input form and output display.

CSS 🎨: Adds responsive and visually appealing styling.

JavaScript ⚙️: Handles fetching data from the weather API and dynamically displaying it to the user.

💡 Features

Enter any city name and get instant weather updates for that location 🌍.

Displays temperature 🌡️ and weather conditions (e.g., clear, cloudy, rainy) ☁️🌧️☀️.

Uses OpenWeatherMap API for real-time weather data.

Clean, minimal, and responsive design 🎨.

🛠️ How It Works

Enter the name of a city in the search field 🌆.

The JavaScript fetches the weather data from the OpenWeatherMap API 🌍.

API: https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=${city}&appid=${apiKey}

The app then displays the temperature and weather conditions for the requested city 🚀.

Error handling for invalid city names or unsuccessful API calls is also included 🚨.

📋 How to Use

Clone the repository to your local machine:

Get an API key from OpenWeatherMap and replace the apiKey placeholder in the JavaScript file with your actual API key 🔑.

Open the index.html file in your browser, enter a city name, and check the weather! 🌤️
